detaileddescription.para: This function is expected to be called cyclically in order to transmit a request and collect a response.

parameterdescription.para: - RecordDataIdentifier of the single service 22/2E diagnose request to be executed

simplesect.para: DCM_E_OK, if LIN diag request is successful
DCM_E_PENDING, if LIN diag request in pending
DCM_E_NOT_OK, if pointer are invalid or for received NRC from LIN

briefdescription.para: Copies data from ConfigLinDiag_Read_Write_DID_buf to the DCM buffer after successful collecting of a slave response.

simplesect.para: Function is expected to be called after successfull execution of LIN DK1/DK2 request, when the ConfigLinDiag_Read_Write_DID_buf is filled with response data and #responseLengthDCM with response data length.
Terminates processing of the DCM request.

parameterdescription.para: - Status of the DCM request operation
- DCM buffer for Read Data By Identifier response data filled with data received from the LIN slave

simplesect.para: DCM_E_OK in case of valid parameter values

DCM_E_NOT_OK in case of invalid paramater values

briefdescription.para: Triggers LIN DK2 request processing for specyfic slave.

simplesect.para: Finished processing of Lin DK2 request. In case of positive response - terminates processing of DCM request positively. In case of negative response - terminates processing of Lin request and provides NRC forwarded form the slave or NRC indicating request processing error.

parameterdescription.para: - Enum value for currently processed slave
- Enum value for currently processed CAN DK2 DID index
- Pointer to DCM buffer containing request data
- Status of the DCM request operation
- DCM buffer for NRC in case of negative response

simplesect.para: DCM_E_OK in case of successful request processing with positive response
DCM_E_NOT_OK in case of request processing error or collecting of a negative response form a LIN DK2 slave
DCM_E_PENDING in case of LIN DK2 request processing in progress

simplesect.title: Globals
simplesect.para: ConfigLinDiag_Read_Write_DID_buf - buffer filled with slave response data in case of positive response
